# =============================================================================
# Houston dev secrets — template for .env.local (gitignored).
#
# One-time setup:   cp .env.example .env.local   then fill in the values below.
#
# SECRETS ONLY live here. Everything non-secret (ports, URLs, tokens shared by
# the whole team) is committed in .env.development — never redefine those keys
# here; the dev doctor refuses to boot if you do, so the team can't drift onto
# different stacks. Run `pnpm dev` and follow the doctor.
# =============================================================================

# --- REQUIRED ----------------------------------------------------------------
# Firebase (GCIP) Web API key for the `gethouston` project — powers Google
# sign-in for the web app's cloud profile. Not secret in the browser sense,
# but kept out of git by policy. Get it from a teammate or the GCIP console
# (Google Cloud → Identity Platform → project `gethouston` → app settings).
FIREBASE_API_KEY=

# --- OPTIONAL (the doctor reports the effect of each, loudly) -----------------
# Seeds every dev engine with an Anthropic credential so agent turns work
# out of the box. Without it, connect a provider in-app per agent.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Connected apps (Gmail, Calendar, ...) via Composio platform mode — one
# project key (free tier at composio.dev → Project Settings → API Keys).
# Without it, integrations are OFF and the doctor says so.
# COMPOSIO_API_KEY=
# Event triggers (routines waking on Gmail/Calendar events) additionally need:
# COMPOSIO_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# Desktop "Report bug" button files to Linear. Without both, the button
# ERRORS with "Bug reporting not configured" — the doctor says so.
# LINEAR_API_KEY=
# LINEAR_TEAM_ID=

# Desktop-app native sign-in (only needed when testing desktop OAuth flows):
# GOOGLE_DESKTOP_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_DESKTOP_CLIENT_SECRET=
# MICROSOFT_DESKTOP_CLIENT_ID=
